# ASTU . BOAP . SEM-II . Course Work repo

General

Show help

docfill --help

Show application description, version, author information and command list.

Show version

docfill --version

Display application version.

---

Database Commands

Initialize example database

docfill db init

Create application database with example schema and demo data.

Initialize custom schema

docfill db schema create \
    --table persons \
    --schema schema.json

Create user-defined table schema.

Show schema

docfill db schema show

Display current database schema.

Drop database

docfill db reset

Delete all tables and recreate the database.

---

Person / Record Commands

List records

docfill data list

Show all records.

View record

docfill data show --id 1

Display a single record.

Add record

docfill data add

Create a new record interactively.

Import record

docfill data import person.json

Import records from file.

Update record

docfill data update --id 1

Modify record fields.

Delete record

docfill data delete --id 1

Remove record.

---

Template Commands

List templates

docfill template list

Show available templates.

Show template

docfill template show invitation

Display template contents.

Add template

docfill template add invitation.docx

Register a new template.

Remove template

docfill template delete invitation

Delete template.

---

Document Generation

Generate document

docfill generate \
    --template invitation \
    --id 1

Generate document for selected person.

Generate all documents

docfill generate \
    --template invitation \
    --all

Generate documents for all records.

Output directory

docfill generate \
    --template invitation \
    --id 1 \
    --output ./generated

Specify custom output directory.

---

Supported Template Formats

* TXT
* Markdown (MD)
* DOCX
* XLS
* XLSX

Planned support:

* PDF import
* ODT
* HTML

---

Examples

docfill db init
docfill data list
docfill generate \
    --template invitation \
    --id 3
docfill generate \
    --template report \
    --all

